  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<strong>Sorcerer Bloodline Power</strong><br/><br/><p>At 15th level, you learn to eschew the use of your hands when casting spells, as a naga would. Whenever you cast an arcane spell with a somatic component, you can do so even with your hands full, by twisting and gyrating your body. This doubles the arcane spell failure chance from your armor (if any), and you can't use this ability if you are pinned or immobile.</p>",
